      • createPushBillboard

        UpsightBillboard createPushBillboard(UpsightContext upsight,
                                     UpsightBillboard.Handler handler)
                              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                     java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Creates and registers a new UpsightBillboard with the default push scope.
        Parameters:
        upsight - The com.upsight.android.UpsightContext.
        handler - The com.upsight.android.marketing.UpsightBillboard.Handler to handle billboard callbacks.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - The scope and handler must be non-null and non-empty.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - An active com.upsight.android.marketing.UpsightBillboard with the same scope already exists. A billboard remains active until either a content view is attached, or com.upsight.android.marketing.UpsightBillboard#destroy() is called.
